text.tspan: The relationship between fertility and HDI through time, 1980 to 2015
The Human Development Index measures human development by combining indicators of a country's health
conditions, living standard and education level (weighted equally).
Source: UNDP (2018), UN Population Division (Fertility) (2015 revision), Population (Gapminder, HYDE(2016) & UN (2019))
